These are the core analytical frameworks professional real estate investors actually use when evaluating deals, markets, and portfolios. If your program teaches these well, students will think much more like institutional investors rather than casual property buyers.

Below are 12 essential real estate investing frameworks you can integrate throughout the track.

12 Core Analytical Frameworks for Real Estate Investing
1. Risk–Return Tradeoff Framework

Every investment must be evaluated based on expected return relative to risk taken.

Key Question

Does this investment provide adequate compensation for the risks involved?

Risks considered

• vacancy
• leverage
• tenant concentration
• interest rate exposure
• market cycle timing

