12. Behavioral Risk Framework

Recognizing how investor psychology affects decisions.

Common biases

• overconfidence
• herd behavior
• recency bias
• loss aversion

Professional investors combat these with:

• structured underwriting
• written investment criteria
• disciplined review processes

