How These Frameworks Strengthen the Course

These frameworks allow students to analyze real estate the way professionals do.

Instead of memorizing definitions, students learn to ask:

• What is the risk-adjusted return?
• What happens if rents fall?
• Where are we in the cycle?
• What does the capital stack look like?
• How sensitive is the investment?

